00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:11,962
Five.

263
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:13,976
Six.

264
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,299
Seven.

265
00:17:16,469 --> 00:17:17,880
Eight.

266
00:17:17,904 --> 00:17:19,748
Nine.

267
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:21,172
Ten.

268
00:17:34,286 --> 00:17:37,800
So you see, members of the jury,

269
00:17:37,824 --> 00:17:43,505
in fairness, you must
return a verdict of not guilty.

270
00:17:43,529 --> 00:17:47,910
Each and every one of
you was staring at that door

271
00:17:47,934 --> 00:17:50,713
because you had
a reasonable doubt

272
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:54,016
that a crime was even committed.

273
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,852
And you must let
this man go free.

274
00:17:56,876 --> 00:18:00,444
He was staring at that
door as hard as you were.

275
00:18:01,948 --> 00:18:03,159
And so were they.

276
00:18:08,955 --> 00:18:11,634
Your Honor, the law is
quite clear on tenants' rights,

277
00:18:11,658 --> 00:18:14,069
and I respectfully ask
you to order the landlord

278
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:16,005
to return my client's
security deposit

279
00:18:16,029 --> 00:18:18,874
in the amount of $750.

280
00:18:18,898 --> 00:18:20,375
Thank you, counselor.

281
00:18:20,399 --> 00:18:21,643
If there's nothing further,

282
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:25,781
I will take the matter
under submission.

283
00:18:25,805 --> 00:18:28,751
We'll receive his decision
by mail in a couple of weeks.

284
00:18:28,775 --> 00:18:29,874
I'll let you know.

285
00:18:31,544 --> 00:18:33,722
<i>I'll tell you the thing
about Clarence.</i>

286
00:18:33,746 --> 00:18:35,324
<i>When you left his stand,</i>

287
00:18:35,348 --> 00:18:37,459
you knew you'd
gotten a shoeshine.

288
00:18:37,483 --> 00:18:39,795
I mean, the man was an artist.

289
00:18:39,819 --> 00:18:42,197
Yep. They don't make
'em like him anymore.

290
00:18:42,221 --> 00:18:45,067
No. And I for one
am gonna miss him.

291
00:18:45,091 --> 00:18:46,501
Hi. Hi.

292
00:18:46,525 --> 00:18:47,736
Morning. Morning, Bert.

293
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,271
See you, Bert. See you.

294
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:50,739
How'd it go?

295
00:18:50,763 --> 00:18:52,274
I got an acquittal.

296
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:53,675
Jury wasn't out long.

297
00:18:53,699 --> 00:18:56,779
Well, justice was
swift this morning.

298
00:18:56,803 --> 00:18:58,781
Let me ask you something. What?

299
00:18:58,805 --> 00:19:00,816
Did it ever occur to
you that we could be

300
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,251
the best father and daughter
team to try a criminal case

301
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:05,309
here in Atlanta?

302
00:19:06,045 --> 00:19:07,255
No, it didn't.

303
00:19:07,279 --> 00:19:08,924
Hi, Phil. PHIL: Hi, Charlene.

304
00:19:08,948 --> 00:19:12,027
Which is my way of
saying, I think that I'm ready

305
00:19:12,051 --> 00:19:13,929
for a little more
challenging litigation.

306
00:19:13,953 --> 00:19:17,165
Charlene, you've only
been out of law school

307
00:19:17,189 --> 00:19:18,601
one year. Two.

308
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:20,202
Well. Hi, John.

309
00:19:20,226 --> 00:19:21,569
Hi. And where am I gonna get

310
00:19:21,593 --> 00:19:23,505
better on-the-job
training than with you,

311
00:19:23,529 --> 00:19:24,740
Dad? Hm.

312
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:28,744
Hey, Wayne, you
are looking good.

313
00:19:28,768 --> 00:19:31,013
Who are all these fellas?

314
00:19:31,037 --> 00:19:32,715
Lawyers.

315
00:19:32,739 --> 00:19:34,316
Stay away from lawyers.

316
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,451
They have ethics, no morals.

317
00:19:36,475 --> 00:19:39,321
Yeah, but they sure do have fun.

318
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:43,325
Where'd you meet 'em?
Met most of 'em at Santino's.

319
00:19:43,349 --> 00:19:44,960
That's a pickup bar, isn't it?

320
00:19:44,984 --> 00:19:46,028
No.

321
00:19:46,052 --> 00:19:48,864
It's where we
yuppies go to unwind.

322
00:19:48,888 --> 00:19:51,633
Haven't you ever seen
a beer commercial?

323
00:19:51,657 --> 00:19:53,068
Hmph.

324
00:19:57,263 --> 00:19:59,107
Bob, how's that new car running?

325
00:19:59,131 --> 00:20:00,442
Running good, Ben.

326
00:20:00,466 --> 00:20:02,378
Good-looking car.

327
00:20:02,402 --> 00:20:04,579
Paid way too much for it.

328
00:20:04,603 --> 00:20:06,949
Harvey Ravanelle's
looking for you, Ben.

329
00:20:06,973 --> 00:20:09,684
What's an important
lawyer like Harvey Ravanelle

330
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:11,228
want with the likes of me?

331
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:13,722
Morning, Hazel.

332
00:20:13,746 --> 00:20:14,723
Hi, Hazel. HAZEL: Hi.

333
00:20:14,747 --> 00:20:16,391
Phones messages
are on your desk,

334
00:20:16,415 --> 00:20:18,627
Charlene's lunch date
has been cancelled,

335
00:20:18,651 --> 00:20:20,529
Mr. and Mrs. Pearson
are in your office,

336
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:23,198
and you forgot to
file your tax form.

337
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,456
Damn. I filed it for you.

338
00:20:26,859 --> 00:20:29,371
Hazel, sometime let's
you and me get married.

339
00:20:29,395 --> 00:20:31,273
Get a new suit
and I'll think about it.

340
00:20:31,297 --> 00:20:33,475
I'm sorry to keep
you folks waiting.

341
00:20:33,499 --> 00:20:35,911
Charlene, this is Mark
and Betty Pearson.

342
00:20:35,935 --> 00:20:38,146
Mark has milk cattle
over at Willow Springs.

343
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:41,083
This is my associate and my
daughter. What can I do for you?

344
00:20:41,107 --> 00:20:44,053
Old man Cornell
said my dog bit him.

345
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:46,521
Says he's gonna sue us in court.

346
00:20:46,545 --> 00:20:48,157
Is that a fact?

347
00:20:49,214 --> 00:20:53,828
Well, we've got four
lines of defenses.

348
00:20:53,852 --> 00:20:56,232
One: my dog doesn't bite.

349
00:20:56,256 --> 00:20:59,501
Two: my dog was
tied up at the time.

350
00:20:59,525 --> 00:21:03,939
Three: I don't think
you really got bit.

351
00:21:03,963 --> 00:21:06,697
Four: I don't have a dog.

352
00:21:08,001 --> 00:21:09,445
My dog don't bite.

353
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:15,005
Yes, ma'am.

354
00:21:16,742 --> 00:21:18,175
Really?

355
00:21:19,144 --> 00:21:20,889
I'll be right with him.

356
00:21:20,913 --> 00:21:23,625
If you'll just go with
my associate here,

357
00:21:23,649 --> 00:21:25,760
she'll draft a
strongly worded letter

358
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:29,364
to disabuse Mr. Cornell
of this fruitless litigation.

359
00:21:29,388 --> 00:21:31,833
Is it gonna be expensive?

360
00:21:31,857 --> 00:21:35,170
Well, her time is
not as dear as mine.

361
00:21:35,194 --> 00:21:37,472
So it's gonna cost you $15.

362
00:21:37,496 --> 00:21:41,442
That's 10 for the letter and
5 for a leash for you dog.

363
00:21:41,466 --> 00:21:43,211
And then I am taking
you out to lunch

364
00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:45,180
so we can discuss our future.

365
00:21:45,204 --> 00:21:46,848
I plan on being unavailable.

366
00:21:46,872 --> 00:21:48,283
Harvey!

367
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:49,885
Sorry to drop in on
you like this, Benny.

368
00:21:49,909 --> 00:21:51,319
Aw, it's a real honor,

369
00:21:51,343 --> 00:21:53,522
your coming all the way
down from your penthouse.

370
00:21:53,546 --> 00:21:55,524
I'm Ben Matlock. Steve Emerson.

371
00:21:55,548 --> 00:21:57,592
Oh, I know my
mother's gonna be green

372
00:21:57,616 --> 00:21:59,027
when she hears I met you.

373
00:21:59,051 --> 00:22:02,431
Ben, our firm represents
Steve's network in this state,

374
00:22:02,455 --> 00:22:03,698
but as you probably know,

375
00:22:03,722 --> 00:22:05,767
Steve here needs a
top defense attorney.

376
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:07,169
It's all anybody
could talk about

377
00:22:07,193 --> 00:22:09,538
down at the courthouse this
morning. Sit down, Mr. Emerson.

378
00:22:09,562 --> 00:22:11,005
Know any of the details, Ben?

379
00:22:11,029 --> 00:22:13,775
Friend of mine in the
DA's office told me about it.

380
00:22:13,799 --> 00:22:15,510
Help yourself to peanuts.

381
00:22:15,534 --> 00:22:19,381
I got 'em in barter from
a client down in Plains.

382
00:22:19,405 --> 00:22:20,716
It's not who you think.

383
00:22:20,740 --> 00:22:24,019
Look, Harvey, with all
due respect to Mr. Matlock,

384
00:22:24,043 --> 00:22:25,721
I have some very close
friends in New York,

385
00:22:25,745 --> 00:22:27,523
and they're excellent
defense attorneys.

386
00:22:27,547 --> 00:22:30,492
I wouldn't do
that if I were you.

387
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:32,428
Why is that?

388
00:22:32,452 --> 00:22:34,896
Well, let me explain
some of your problems.

389
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:37,533
First off, you got the
disposition of the jury

390
00:22:37,557 --> 00:22:38,867
to consider.

391
00:22:38,891 --> 00:22:41,770
They look at you as a
fast-talking TV personality

392
00:22:41,794 --> 00:22:43,071
from New York.

393
00:22:43,095 --> 00:22:45,040
And you're rich.
I'm hardly rich.

394
00:22:45,064 --> 00:22:48,310
According to the standards of
folks around here, you're rich.

395
00:22:48,334 --> 00:22:52,147
And you got another first strike
against you: you're an outsider.

396
00:22:52,171 --> 00:22:54,649
You need a local boy,
somebody who's good.

397
00:22:54,673 --> 00:22:56,184
Steve,

398
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:59,087
Ben here has a
record in criminal cases

399
00:22:59,111 --> 00:23:00,722
probably second to none.

400
00:23:00,746 --> 00:23:03,125
He's handled murder
trials all over the country.

401
00:23:03,149 --> 00:23:05,727
Harvey, don't...
Don't press the man.

402
00:23:05,751 --> 00:23:07,896
Harvey, I'm in
deep trouble here.

403
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:10,040
If I were in your
spot, I'd want Ben.

404
00:23:10,957 --> 00:23:13,068
Wait a minute.

405
00:23:13,092 --> 00:23:15,770
I said you need
somebody<i> like</i> me.

406
00:23:15,794 --> 00:23:17,773
I didn't say I'd take the case.

407
00:23:17,797 --> 00:23:19,074
What?

408
00:23:19,098 --> 00:23:21,076
Your situation doesn't
sound too good to me.

409
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:22,478
Ben, we need you.

410
00:23:22,502 --> 00:23:24,713
Harvey, I've got my
reputation to consider.

411
00:23:24,737 --> 00:23:26,615
Money is no object here.

412
00:23:26,639 --> 00:23:28,872
Money never is.

413
00:23:30,643 --> 00:23:31,954
How much cash you got?

414
00:23:31,978 --> 00:23:36,125
About 50,000. Any
bonds? Securities?

415
00:23:36,149 --> 00:23:37,314
Another 50.

416
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:40,596
That'll do as a retainer.

417
00:23:40,620 --> 00:23:43,031
A retainer?

418
00:23:43,055 --> 00:23:44,699
Look, at it this way, Steve.

419
00:23:44,723 --> 00:23:47,402
If I win, it'll be worth it.

420
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:49,337
If I don't, they take you

421
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:52,107
to the Georgia Diagnostic
and Classification Center

422
00:23:52,131 --> 00:23:54,209
over near Jackson and
they electrocute you.

423
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:56,353
I think you made
your point, okay?

424
00:23:56,969 --> 00:23:59,514
Harvey,

425
00:23:59,538 --> 00:24:01,583
thanks for throwing
some business my way.

426
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:02,684
I appreciate it.

427
00:24:02,708 --> 00:24:04,675
I'll talk to you later, Steve.

428
00:24:05,911 --> 00:24:08,590
We got a lot of talking to do.

429
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:12,026
You gotta tell me everything
that happened that night,

430
00:24:12,050 --> 00:24:15,563
anything important
I should know.

431
00:24:15,587 --> 00:24:18,299
Well, my marriage
to Linda was stormy.

432
00:24:18,323 --> 00:24:21,469
The divorce was even worse.

433
00:24:21,493 --> 00:24:23,927
But I loved her.
I didn't kill her.

434
00:24:25,531 --> 00:24:28,443
I understand you've got an
alibi for the time of the murder.

435
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:30,278
That's a privileged
news communication.

436
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:31,713
I can't reveal the source.

437
00:24:31,737 --> 00:24:33,582
Even if it means your own neck?

438
00:24:33,606 --> 00:24:35,238
I gave the man my word.

439
00:24:37,343 --> 00:24:40,122
I don't have to tell you this
is gonna be an uphill battle.

440
00:24:40,146 --> 00:24:43,458
Prosecution has all the cards.

441
00:24:43,482 --> 00:24:45,682
I'll give it the
best shot I got.

442
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:50,899
Next to injustice,
I hate losing.

443
00:24:56,895 --> 00:24:58,328
Thank you.

444
00:25:02,802 --> 00:25:05,280
Ben, Hazel said you wanted
me here for the arraignment.

445
00:25:05,304 --> 00:25:07,404
This is Steve Emerson.

446
00:25:09,342 --> 00:25:13,109
My daughter, Charlene, will
be associate counsel on this.

447
00:25:13,779 --> 00:25:15,390
How do you do?

448
00:25:15,414 --> 00:25:20,028
I am so pleased to be working
on your case, Mr. Emerson.

449
00:25:20,052 --> 00:25:21,396
I'm delighted also.

450
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:24,232
You're Ben Matlock, right?

451
00:25:24,256 --> 00:25:26,267
Yes, sir. I've heard
a lot about you.

452
00:25:26,291 --> 00:25:29,538
Burton Hawkins. I'll be
prosecuting this case.

453
00:25:29,562 --> 00:25:31,828
Can we talk, please?

454
00:25:34,733 --> 00:25:39,348
First of all, I don't wanna
cut any deals on this one.

455
00:25:39,372 --> 00:25:42,050
I'm asking for murder one.

456
00:25:42,074 --> 00:25:44,318
What else? "Else"?!

457
00:25:44,342 --> 00:25:46,387
What are you...?
You said, "First of all."

458
00:25:46,411 --> 00:25:48,089
What's second?

459
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:49,758
Aha.

460
00:25:49,782 --> 00:25:51,092
How soon can we try this case?

461
00:25:51,116 --> 00:25:53,228
Soon as you like.

462
00:25:53,252 --> 00:25:55,931
<i>"People of the State of
Georgia v. Steve Emerson."</i>

463
00:25:55,955 --> 00:26:00,068
Case number F81-500.

464
00:26:00,092 --> 00:26:02,504
Benjamin Matlock for
the defense, Your Honor.

465
00:26:02,528 --> 00:26:04,673
All right. MATLOCK:
Defendant is present.

466
00:26:04,697 --> 00:26:05,874
He's been informed

467
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:08,209
of his constitutional
and statutory rights,

468
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,511
received a copy
of the indictment,

469
00:26:10,535 --> 00:26:13,482
waives further reading thereof.

470
00:26:13,506 --> 00:26:15,249
Defendant pleads
not guilty, Your Honor,

471
00:26:15,273 --> 00:26:17,019
requests a jury trial.

472
00:26:17,043 --> 00:26:18,653
The time is waived.

473
00:26:18,677 --> 00:26:21,189
What about, uh, September 16th?

474
00:26:21,213 --> 00:26:23,925
Fine with my client.

475
00:26:23,949 --> 00:26:25,493
Prosecution agrees.

476
00:26:25,517 --> 00:26:29,264
All right, this case is set
for trial on September 16th,

477
00:26:29,288 --> 00:26:33,468
Courtroom 203 of the Criminal
Division of Superior Court,

478
00:26:33,492 --> 00:26:35,137
9 a.m.

479
00:26:35,161 --> 00:26:38,540
Mr. Emerson, is it true you're
protecting a news source?

480
00:26:38,564 --> 00:26:40,008
Why were you here in Atlanta?

481
00:26:40,032 --> 00:26:42,210
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

482
00:26:42,234 --> 00:26:43,878
I can only answer
one question at a time.

483
00:26:43,902 --> 00:26:45,780
Mr. Emerson has no comment.

484
00:26:45,804 --> 00:26:47,882
What's your strategy?
Did he have an alibi?

485
00:26:47,906 --> 00:26:50,018
Hold it, hold it.

486
00:26:50,042 --> 00:26:51,452
All I'll say is,

487
00:26:51,476 --> 00:26:54,989
the State has seen fit to assign
their most brilliant prosecutor,

488
00:26:55,013 --> 00:26:56,691
Burton Hawkins, to this trial.

489
00:26:56,715 --> 00:26:59,360
Now, they don't assign a
man like "Death Row" Hawkins

490
00:26:59,384 --> 00:27:02,163
unless they feel they got a
lot of problems with their case.

491
00:27:02,187 --> 00:27:03,865
And they may have
a couple of problems

492
00:27:03,889 --> 00:27:05,333
they don't know about yet.

493
00:27:05,357 --> 00:27:06,968
That's all. Thank you.

494
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:12,607
They're your batteries,
boys. That's all.

495
00:27:12,631 --> 00:27:15,577
Step into my office. Come on.

496
00:27:15,601 --> 00:27:17,311
Now, this is important.

497
00:27:17,335 --> 00:27:20,148
I don't want you making
any statements to the press.

498
00:27:20,172 --> 00:27:21,716
Absolutely none. Why is that?

499
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:23,852
I don't want this
case tried on TV

500
00:27:23,876 --> 00:27:25,954
before we get it
in the courtroom.

501
00:27:25,978 --> 00:27:28,089
All right. What about
this prosecutor?

502
00:27:28,113 --> 00:27:29,758
How good is he? I don't
know much about him.

503
00:27:29,782 --> 00:27:31,525
He's sorta new. But
he must be good,

504
00:27:31,549 --> 00:27:32,894
or he wouldn't be on this case.

505
00:27:32,918 --> 00:27:35,163
Oh, he's good. He's got
a great conviction rate.

506
00:27:35,187 --> 00:27:38,855
DA's office thinks
that he's a real comer.

507
00:27:41,894 --> 00:27:44,094
It's all right. She's a lawyer.

508
00:27:45,197 --> 00:27:47,309
What happens now?

509
00:27:47,333 --> 00:27:49,811
I spoke with a friend of
mine who should know.

510
00:27:49,835 --> 00:27:52,280
And he hasn't heard
anything about the syndicate

511
00:27:52,304 --> 00:27:53,949
being involved in
state government.

512
00:27:53,973 --> 00:27:55,583
So I've gotta find the
man you were with

513
00:27:55,607 --> 00:27:57,752
the night of the
murder, and fast.

514
00:27:57,776 --> 00:27:59,254
Charlene here's gonna check out

