00:31:03,328 --> 00:31:04,805
Besides,

584
00:31:04,829 --> 00:31:07,475
I don't know anything
about Linda's personal life.

585
00:31:07,499 --> 00:31:11,246
Sorry.

586
00:31:20,245 --> 00:31:24,559
It's Steve Emerson down
in Atlanta. Is Jimmy in?

587
00:31:24,583 --> 00:31:26,694
Jimmy, I need you to express
me Linda's banking records

588
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:28,930
first thing in the
morning, okay?

589
00:31:28,954 --> 00:31:30,365
Now, look, spare
me the legalities.

590
00:31:30,389 --> 00:31:32,400
You've been our accountant
what? Eight, nine years?

591
00:31:32,424 --> 00:31:33,735
Well, you'll stay my accountant

592
00:31:33,759 --> 00:31:36,637
if you give me
those computer runs.

593
00:31:36,661 --> 00:31:38,173
What are you doing here?

594
00:31:38,197 --> 00:31:40,641
Same thing you're doing,
only I'm supposed to be here.

595
00:31:43,936 --> 00:31:45,246
Phil.

596
00:31:45,270 --> 00:31:46,381
Listen, I need all the clips

597
00:31:46,405 --> 00:31:47,949
out of Research
you have on Linda.

598
00:31:47,973 --> 00:31:49,918
Particularly anything
out of Atlanta,

599
00:31:49,942 --> 00:31:51,987
with a heavy underline
on the social stuff.

600
00:31:52,011 --> 00:31:55,044
I'm gonna call you back
tomorrow, okay? Thanks.

601
00:31:56,215 --> 00:31:59,094
Ben isn't gonna like this.

602
00:31:59,118 --> 00:32:02,130
Well, Ben isn't gonna
be electrocuted, is he?

603
00:32:02,154 --> 00:32:04,032
Steve, I, uh...

604
00:32:04,056 --> 00:32:06,001
I got those tapes up
you wanted to see.

605
00:32:06,025 --> 00:32:08,069
Great.

606
00:32:08,093 --> 00:32:09,270
You coming?

607
00:32:09,294 --> 00:32:10,627
Oh, yeah.

608
00:32:13,132 --> 00:32:14,942
You wanna run that tape, please?

609
00:32:14,966 --> 00:32:17,812
Roll the A machine, please.

610
00:32:17,836 --> 00:32:19,180
What are you looking for?

611
00:32:19,204 --> 00:32:21,783
A clue to whoever
put that gun in my car.

612
00:32:21,807 --> 00:32:22,918
Oh, listen, I, uh,

613
00:32:22,942 --> 00:32:25,687
ordered up some additional
footage from WPKS.

614
00:32:25,711 --> 00:32:26,988
What have you got?

615
00:32:27,012 --> 00:32:29,124
Her boyfriend. Uh,
uh, what's his name?

616
00:32:29,148 --> 00:32:30,691
Lockwood. Lockwood. Yeah, yeah.

617
00:32:30,715 --> 00:32:33,028
Well, he claims he
was at a fundraiser.

618
00:32:33,052 --> 00:32:34,985
Let's see if he's
telling the truth.

619
00:32:36,855 --> 00:32:38,800
Roll the B machine, please.

620
00:32:38,824 --> 00:32:40,635
You suspect Lockwood?

621
00:32:40,659 --> 00:32:43,071
Hey, listen, at this point
I suspect everybody.

622
00:32:43,095 --> 00:32:45,506
He told the police he
never left the ballroom.

623
00:32:45,530 --> 00:32:47,642
Well, looks like his
alibi is better than mine.

624
00:32:47,666 --> 00:32:50,144
Yeah.

625
00:32:50,168 --> 00:32:51,378
Okay, listen, Steve,

626
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:53,648
if you need anything,
let me know, huh?

627
00:32:53,672 --> 00:32:55,382
Morris, switch
back to the first tape.

628
00:32:55,406 --> 00:32:57,886
Roll the A machine
again, please.

629
00:32:58,243 --> 00:32:59,487
You might wanna find out

630
00:32:59,511 --> 00:33:01,789
where her fellow
anchorman was that night.

631
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,190
Nelson White?

632
00:33:03,214 --> 00:33:04,659
And what about helpful McCall?

633
00:33:04,683 --> 00:33:07,629
Why is he sticking
his neck out for you?

634
00:33:07,653 --> 00:33:11,198
Maybe he thinks
I'm a terrific guy.

635
00:33:11,222 --> 00:33:14,201
I already asked him. He
said he was home, alone.

636
00:33:14,225 --> 00:33:16,070
Thought he was married.

637
00:33:16,094 --> 00:33:19,107
Separated. Where do you want
to have dinner tomorrow night?

638
00:33:19,131 --> 00:33:21,109
I didn't know that we were

639
00:33:21,133 --> 00:33:23,244
having dinner together
tomorrow night.

640
00:33:23,268 --> 00:33:25,814
I thought you wanted a
full background on Linda.

641
00:33:25,838 --> 00:33:27,448
I do.

642
00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:31,119
Have dinner in my hotel
dining room around 8.

643
00:33:31,143 --> 00:33:32,453
It's for you.

644
00:33:32,477 --> 00:33:34,837
I'll take that in
Linda's dressing room.

645
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:37,127
Gonna tell Daddy on me?

646
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:39,227
Absolutely.

647
00:34:02,174 --> 00:34:04,418
Which one of you
is the toughest?

648
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:07,121
What's it to you?

649
00:34:07,145 --> 00:34:09,256
Here's a ten spot.

650
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:11,325
I come out and my car
hasn't been touched,

651
00:34:11,349 --> 00:34:13,461
there'll be another
one just like it.

652
00:34:13,485 --> 00:34:15,284
You got it.

653
00:34:20,359 --> 00:34:23,771
<i>♪ You always took The last ♪</i>

654
00:34:23,795 --> 00:34:27,975
<i>♪ Of my pride ♪</i>

655
00:34:27,999 --> 00:34:32,447
<i>♪ I realized ♪</i>

656
00:34:32,471 --> 00:34:35,016
<i>♪ You hate goodbye ♪</i>

657
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,217
Yeah?

658
00:34:36,241 --> 00:34:38,853
Ben, now this is
exactly the reason

659
00:34:38,877 --> 00:34:41,022
why I don't like
investigative work.

660
00:34:41,046 --> 00:34:43,625
Take a look around here.

661
00:34:43,649 --> 00:34:46,027
One: this is the kind of place

662
00:34:46,051 --> 00:34:48,029
where you can catch
death like a cold.

663
00:34:48,053 --> 00:34:51,099
And I assume there's a
powerful reason why we're here.

664
00:34:51,123 --> 00:34:53,201
Two:

665
00:34:53,225 --> 00:34:55,603
you never know when
one of these yahoos

666
00:34:55,627 --> 00:34:57,439
is gonna get it in his
skull to mess with you.

667
00:34:57,463 --> 00:35:00,108
Tyler, why are we here?

668
00:35:00,132 --> 00:35:01,342
All right.

669
00:35:01,366 --> 00:35:03,411
I put the word out
to some people

670
00:35:03,435 --> 00:35:07,481
that we are looking for
a very special songbird.

671
00:35:07,505 --> 00:35:09,483
I got a message on
my answering machine

672
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:12,887
that said if we came
here, we'd meet somebody.

673
00:35:12,911 --> 00:35:16,457
You think the person we're
looking for could be here now?

674
00:35:16,481 --> 00:35:18,760
Well, either that,

675
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:21,351
or they sent someone
to scout us out first.

676
00:35:25,190 --> 00:35:26,989
You girls lost?

677
00:35:28,526 --> 00:35:31,939
You see what I
mean? It never fails.

678
00:35:31,963 --> 00:35:34,075
I asked you a question, Leroy.

679
00:35:34,099 --> 00:35:35,676
Of course you realize

680
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:39,047
that because of this scholar,
we have blown our meeting.

681
00:35:39,071 --> 00:35:40,837
No one's gonna talk to us now.

682
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:46,487
Let's you and me get it on, son.

683
00:35:46,511 --> 00:35:48,622
You know, friend? You're
right. You made your point.

684
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:49,857
We're leaving. Excuse us.

685
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:52,581
You ain't going...

686
00:35:55,754 --> 00:35:57,787
Damn, I hate this business.

687
00:36:02,460 --> 00:36:03,938
Ladies and gentlemen,

688
00:36:03,962 --> 00:36:06,473
you have just seen
a demonstration

689
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:08,710
of what can be done
if you're accosted

690
00:36:08,734 --> 00:36:10,344
as my friend here was.

691
00:36:10,368 --> 00:36:12,847
But what if you're
not an ex-Marine?

692
00:36:12,871 --> 00:36:15,516
What if you're the one
to suffer bodily harm?

693
00:36:15,540 --> 00:36:18,019
The smartest thing you
can do is come to see me.

694
00:36:18,043 --> 00:36:21,488
Benjamin Matlock, fully
licensed attorney at law.

695
00:36:21,512 --> 00:36:26,093
Your personal injuries
can be worth big money.

696
00:36:26,117 --> 00:36:27,761
Night, all.

697
00:36:27,785 --> 00:36:33,122
<i>♪ You hate goodbye ♪</i>

698
00:36:42,534 --> 00:36:45,880
Well, as far as Linda's
co-workers are concerned,

699
00:36:45,904 --> 00:36:49,383
I think that we should take a
closer look at McCall and White.

700
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:51,552
Why don't you nose
around the TV station?

701
00:36:51,576 --> 00:36:53,855
The weatherman loves to talk.

