751
00:38:38,482 --> 00:38:40,583
Right. I'll be there.

752
00:38:56,401 --> 00:38:57,911
This is ridiculous.

753
00:38:57,935 --> 00:39:00,281
How can they
treat you like that?

754
00:39:00,305 --> 00:39:02,182
Beg pardon? I'm amazed.

755
00:39:02,206 --> 00:39:03,451
You are?

756
00:39:03,475 --> 00:39:06,787
I am astounded that a
scientist of your stature

757
00:39:06,811 --> 00:39:08,156
is forced to dress like that.

758
00:39:08,180 --> 00:39:10,858
What, do they want you
to look like good weather?

759
00:39:10,882 --> 00:39:11,959
Who are you?

760
00:39:11,983 --> 00:39:13,994
I'm Tyler Hudson,
Dr. Farnsworth.

761
00:39:14,018 --> 00:39:16,497
I've been a fan of yours
since you were on radio,

762
00:39:16,521 --> 00:39:18,466
doing forecasts out
there at the airport.

763
00:39:18,490 --> 00:39:20,601
I never missed your show.

764
00:39:20,625 --> 00:39:21,902
If I don't go along,

765
00:39:21,926 --> 00:39:23,937
they'll get some kid
in here to replace me.

766
00:39:23,961 --> 00:39:25,706
Mm. Uh, you work here?

767
00:39:25,730 --> 00:39:27,207
No, no. I work for
a couple of lawyers.

768
00:39:27,231 --> 00:39:30,944
But look, I am such a fan.

769
00:39:30,968 --> 00:39:32,680
Could I buy you a cup of coffee?

770
00:39:32,704 --> 00:39:35,783
I saw this fantastic
little sidewalk cafe

771
00:39:35,807 --> 00:39:37,585
around the corner.
It would be great.

772
00:39:37,609 --> 00:39:39,320
If it doesn't rain.

