1032
00:54:36,940 --> 00:54:38,207
You all right?

1033
00:54:39,843 --> 00:54:40,887
I suppose.

1034
00:54:40,911 --> 00:54:42,777
You've been awfully quiet.

1035
00:54:44,048 --> 00:54:45,826
I guess tonight

1036
00:54:45,850 --> 00:54:48,290
reminded me of those
last few months with Linda.

1037
00:54:49,853 --> 00:54:51,965
All the paparazzi.

1038
00:54:51,989 --> 00:54:55,234
I'm sorry I lost my temper.

1039
00:54:55,258 --> 00:54:57,871
It's all right. No,
it's not all right.

1040
00:54:57,895 --> 00:55:00,374
I'm used to taking the heat.

1041
00:55:00,398 --> 00:55:04,110
I guess this just affected
me more than I realized.

1042
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:05,533
You're only human.

1043
00:55:07,370 --> 00:55:11,384
One day I'm a hotshot
TV news correspondent.

1044
00:55:11,408 --> 00:55:14,320
Next day I'm on
trial for murder,

1045
00:55:14,344 --> 00:55:17,491
already convicted in the
press and my life is on hold.

1046
00:55:17,515 --> 00:55:18,814
Film at 11.

1047
00:55:22,552 --> 00:55:24,631
You are doing the smart thing.

1048
00:55:24,655 --> 00:55:26,233
You're taking action.

1049
00:55:26,257 --> 00:55:28,168
I admire you for that.

1050
00:55:28,192 --> 00:55:29,691
You know, you're terrific.

1051
00:55:35,466 --> 00:55:37,077
I have to go.

1052
00:55:37,101 --> 00:55:38,712
You really have to go?

1053
00:55:38,736 --> 00:55:41,180
It's a big day tomorrow.

1054
00:55:41,204 --> 00:55:43,305
Ben does like to start early.

1055
00:55:58,689 --> 00:56:00,888
Well, good night.

1056
00:56:02,393 --> 00:56:03,525
Good night.

1057
00:56:04,961 --> 00:56:06,039
Thanks again.

1058
00:56:06,063 --> 00:56:08,330
Yeah.

1059
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:13,213
Uh, ha.

1060
00:56:13,237 --> 00:56:15,270
I really do have to go.

1061
00:56:19,243 --> 00:56:20,387
Bye.

1062
00:56:20,411 --> 00:56:22,177
Good night.

1063
00:56:32,490 --> 00:56:36,069
Well, this is just perfect.

1064
00:56:36,093 --> 00:56:40,206
Why in the hell didn't he shoot
somebody while he was at it?

1065
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:42,608
You really can't blame
him, Ben. They're vultures.

1066
00:56:42,632 --> 00:56:45,711
Charlene, this paper's gonna
be in every checkout line

1067
00:56:45,735 --> 00:56:47,614
in every supermarket
in this city.

1068
00:56:47,638 --> 00:56:49,149
Do you know how
many prospective jurors

1069
00:56:49,173 --> 00:56:50,817
are gonna see this? All of 'em.

1070
00:56:50,841 --> 00:56:53,353
The<i> Informer</i> is gonna
print whatever it wants

1071
00:56:53,377 --> 00:56:54,688
whether it's true or not.

1072
00:56:54,712 --> 00:56:55,889
You mean like: "The two of 'em

1073
00:56:55,913 --> 00:56:59,214
were entwined in
intimate conversation"?

1074
00:57:00,417 --> 00:57:01,961
Just what are you suggesting?

1075
00:57:01,985 --> 00:57:04,797
I'm suggesting you
used very poor judgment

1076
00:57:04,821 --> 00:57:06,766
going up to his room
after what happened.

1077
00:57:06,790 --> 00:57:08,801
What if they'd photographed
you coming out of there?

1078
00:57:08,825 --> 00:57:10,670
Are you worried about
his reputation or mine?

1079
00:57:10,694 --> 00:57:12,138
Just how involved are you?

1080
00:57:12,162 --> 00:57:13,874
Are you asking as
a lawyer or a father?

1081
00:57:13,898 --> 00:57:14,875
Both.

1082
00:57:14,899 --> 00:57:16,176
Well, the answer to both of you

1083
00:57:16,200 --> 00:57:17,343
is that I resent the question.

1084
00:57:17,367 --> 00:57:18,812
That's not an answer.

1085
00:57:18,836 --> 00:57:21,035
Oh, yes it is.

1086
00:57:23,073 --> 00:57:24,617
Yes?

1087
00:57:24,641 --> 00:57:26,552
Send him in.

1088
00:57:26,576 --> 00:57:28,888
Our favorite client.

1089
00:57:28,912 --> 00:57:30,624
I was just reading about you.

1090
00:57:30,648 --> 00:57:32,592
What's all this about you
and Billy Ray Webber?

1091
00:57:32,616 --> 00:57:33,993
I just saw it on the news.

1092
00:57:34,017 --> 00:57:35,895
He's the guy I was with
the night Linda was killed.

1093
00:57:35,919 --> 00:57:38,297
What happened? He's dead.

1094
00:57:38,321 --> 00:57:41,134
And the mob didn't do it. I
was talking with one of 'em.

1095
00:57:41,158 --> 00:57:43,369
They're as anxious to find
out who did it as we are.

1096
00:57:43,393 --> 00:57:44,704
Well, what do we do now?

1097
00:57:44,728 --> 00:57:46,640
I'll tell you what<i> you</i> do now.

1098
00:57:46,664 --> 00:57:49,175
You give me your
word you'll do as I say,

1099
00:57:49,199 --> 00:57:51,600
when I say it, or get
yourself another lawyer.

1100
00:57:54,838 --> 00:57:56,598
All right, you've got it.

1101
00:57:58,142 --> 00:58:00,787
Jury selection starts
Monday. We have no alibi,

1102
00:58:00,811 --> 00:58:03,456
and no way to establish
reasonable doubt.

1103
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:06,860
What we need is a
bright idea, and soon.

1104
00:58:06,884 --> 00:58:08,094
Good morning, people.

1105
00:58:08,118 --> 00:58:10,763
And have I got some
hot news for you.

1106
00:58:10,787 --> 00:58:12,499
We are in the
market for hot news.

1107
00:58:12,523 --> 00:58:14,467
Yeah, well here it is.

1108
00:58:14,491 --> 00:58:16,870
Now, maybe no one
listens to the weatherman.

1109
00:58:16,894 --> 00:58:20,340
But the weatherman sure
listens to everyone else.

1110
00:58:20,364 --> 00:58:24,210
Seems our Linda Coolidge
was one very ambitious lady.

1111
00:58:24,234 --> 00:58:25,512
Now, I hate to say it, pal,

1112
00:58:25,536 --> 00:58:28,269
but her apartment
had a swinging door.

1113
00:58:30,107 --> 00:58:31,684
She had two rejected lovers

1114
00:58:31,708 --> 00:58:34,154
on the staff with
motives for murder:

1115
00:58:34,178 --> 00:58:35,677
McCall and White.

1116
00:58:36,580 --> 00:58:38,157
You got any proof?

1117
00:58:38,181 --> 00:58:39,459
No.

1118
00:58:39,483 --> 00:58:41,995
But evidently there was
some type of red leather diary?

1119
00:58:42,019 --> 00:58:44,564
Yeah.

1120
00:58:44,588 --> 00:58:47,133
It was about so big.

1121
00:58:47,157 --> 00:58:49,469
She wrote everything in it.
Her ideas, her appointments.

1122
00:58:49,493 --> 00:58:51,137
She never went
anywhere without it.

1123
00:58:51,161 --> 00:58:52,794
Did you see it the
night of the murder?

1124
00:58:54,331 --> 00:58:56,809
Yeah, it was on
her coffee table.

1125
00:58:56,833 --> 00:58:59,746
Well, it's not there now,
and the police don't have it.

1126
00:58:59,770 --> 00:59:01,381
Well, if it was
there when you left,

1127
00:59:01,405 --> 00:59:03,883
and gone by the time
the police got there,

1128
00:59:03,907 --> 00:59:05,987
the murderer
might have taken it.

1129
00:59:06,744 --> 00:59:08,054
Leaves us nowhere.

1130
00:59:08,078 --> 00:59:10,445
Not necessarily.

1131
00:59:12,382 --> 00:59:15,384
I think I just got
a bright idea.

1132
00:59:22,559 --> 00:59:23,970
You reside in Atlanta,

1133
00:59:23,994 --> 00:59:26,105
and you are an
accountant, is that correct?

1134
00:59:26,129 --> 00:59:27,641
That's right, sir.

1135
00:59:27,665 --> 00:59:29,643
We are endeavoring
to impanel a jury

1136
00:59:29,667 --> 00:59:32,645
to try an indictment
against Steve Emerson.

1137
00:59:32,669 --> 00:59:34,680
That indictment charges him

1138
00:59:34,704 --> 00:59:36,583
with the murder
of Linda Coolidge.

1139
00:59:36,607 --> 00:59:39,085
Have you read anything
about this in the paper?

1140
00:59:39,109 --> 00:59:40,486
Or have you heard
anything about it

1141
00:59:40,510 --> 00:59:41,721
over the various news media?

1142
00:59:41,745 --> 00:59:42,989
Oh, yes.

1143
00:59:43,013 --> 00:59:44,157
Take a look at this.

1144
00:59:44,181 --> 00:59:47,327
I see. Mr. Cooper...
What do you think?

1145
00:59:47,351 --> 00:59:49,829
Terrific.

1146
00:59:49,853 --> 00:59:51,664
Go to it. But watch your step.

1147
00:59:51,688 --> 00:59:54,334
Or any conscientious scruples
which would prevent you

1148
00:59:54,358 --> 00:59:55,935
from returning a verdict

1149
00:59:55,959 --> 00:59:57,670
which would make it
mandatory upon the court

1150
00:59:57,694 --> 00:59:59,905
to impose the death sentence?

1151
00:59:59,929 --> 01:00:01,240
No, sir.

1152
01:00:01,264 --> 01:00:02,931
Thank you.

1153
01:00:04,668 --> 01:00:06,588
Mr. Matlock, your witness.

1154
01:00:10,473 --> 01:00:11,906
Mr. Cooper,

1155
01:00:14,010 --> 01:00:16,723
we didn't get you up too early
to come down here, did we?

1156
01:00:16,747 --> 01:00:18,124
No, I'm an early riser.

1157
01:00:18,148 --> 01:00:19,659
Yeah, me too.

1158
01:00:19,683 --> 01:00:21,761
Gives me a chance
to read the papers

1159
01:00:21,785 --> 01:00:23,129
and look at the news on TV.

1160
01:00:23,153 --> 01:00:24,864
Is that the same
for you? Oh, yes.

1161
01:00:24,888 --> 01:00:26,432
Yeah.

1162
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:28,000
You were telling Mr. Hawkins

1163
01:00:28,024 --> 01:00:31,404
that, uh, you read something
about this case in the paper.

1164
01:00:31,428 --> 01:00:34,173
Are you a regular
subscriber to any newspaper?

1165
01:00:34,197 --> 01:00:35,708
We get the <i>Atlanta Constitution.</i>

1166
01:00:35,732 --> 01:00:36,709
Uh, we get the<i> News.</i>

1167
01:00:36,733 --> 01:00:38,944
We get the<i> Weekly Courier.</i>

1168
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:40,647
And so I take it
from time to time

1169
01:00:40,671 --> 01:00:43,516
you've read something about
this case in those papers.

1170
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:44,772
Oh, that's right.

1171
01:00:46,810 --> 01:00:49,622
Does your wife ever bring
home the<i> National Informer</i>?

1172
01:00:49,646 --> 01:00:51,758
Oh. Heh. Sometimes.

1173
01:00:51,782 --> 01:00:53,326
Yeah.

1174
01:00:53,350 --> 01:00:56,062
What do you think about
these papers and the TV news?

1175
01:00:56,086 --> 01:00:58,331
You think they've done a
reliable job covering this case?

1176
01:00:58,355 --> 01:00:59,966
I'd say so.

1177
01:00:59,990 --> 01:01:01,968
You tend to believe it.

1178
01:01:01,992 --> 01:01:03,758
Yes.

1179
01:01:06,062 --> 01:01:08,674
Did you see last
week's<i> Informer?</i>

1180
01:01:08,698 --> 01:01:10,843
The one with the
headline that said,

1181
01:01:10,867 --> 01:01:14,202
"Psychic Says Emerson
Killed Coolidge."

1182
01:01:15,205 --> 01:01:17,271
Yes. Uh...

1183
01:01:20,443 --> 01:01:25,091
Uh... Your Honor,

1184
01:01:25,115 --> 01:01:27,126
we have a real problem here.

1185
01:01:27,150 --> 01:01:29,762
If, uh, Mr. Cooper
read that article

1186
01:01:29,786 --> 01:01:30,930
and believes what he read,

1187
01:01:30,954 --> 01:01:33,733
then he can hardly be
considered impartial.

1188
01:01:33,757 --> 01:01:36,535
Now, on that ground, I
have no choice but to request

1189
01:01:36,559 --> 01:01:38,526
that he be excused for cause.

1190
01:01:40,431 --> 01:01:42,431
You're excused for
cause, Mr. Cooper.

1191
01:01:43,800 --> 01:01:45,433
Go the the second floor, please.

1192
01:01:50,674 --> 01:01:52,352
They call it, ahem,
selecting the jury.

1193
01:01:52,376 --> 01:01:53,486
You don't select the jury.

1194
01:01:53,510 --> 01:01:55,220
You kick off the ones
you really don't want

1195
01:01:55,244 --> 01:01:57,378
and what's left is the jury.

1196
01:01:58,581 --> 01:02:00,593
Any luck tying Ernie
Marzell into this case?

1197
01:02:00,617 --> 01:02:01,861
Not yet.

1198
01:02:01,885 --> 01:02:04,297
Well, if... If he's involved
in state government,

1199
01:02:04,321 --> 01:02:05,932
somebody's got to know it.

1200
01:02:05,956 --> 01:02:07,934
Well, I'll put out a few
feelers. I'll stay in touch.

1201
01:02:07,958 --> 01:02:09,702
Right.

1202
01:02:09,726 --> 01:02:11,538
<i>Jury selection continues</i>

1203
01:02:11,562 --> 01:02:13,106
in the Emerson/Coolidge
murder case

1204
01:02:13,130 --> 01:02:15,608
with a trial expected
to begin on Monday.

1205
01:02:15,632 --> 01:02:16,943
I'm Nelson White,

1206
01:02:16,967 --> 01:02:19,345
and we'll look for you
at our 6:00 news roundup

1207
01:02:19,369 --> 01:02:20,768
this evening.

1208
01:02:21,971 --> 01:02:23,349
And you're clear.

1209
01:02:23,373 --> 01:02:24,818
Very nice, Mr. White, sir.

1210
01:02:24,842 --> 01:02:26,074
I'll take that for you.

1211
01:02:32,516 --> 01:02:34,294
Excuse me, Mr. White.

1212
01:02:34,318 --> 01:02:36,096
If you want to talk to
me, use a subpoena.

1213
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:38,164
Oh, no, we don't wanna do that.

1214
01:02:38,188 --> 01:02:40,400
Well, maybe we do.

1215
01:02:40,424 --> 01:02:43,202
I mean, you've become such
an important figure in this case.

1216
01:02:44,328 --> 01:02:45,772
I can't imagine why.

1217
01:02:45,796 --> 01:02:47,874
Because of your affair
with Linda Coolidge.

1218
01:02:47,898 --> 01:02:49,576
Who told you that?

1219
01:02:49,600 --> 01:02:53,546
I'm sure you must
recognize this.

1220
01:02:53,570 --> 01:02:54,570
Don't you?

1221
01:02:55,939 --> 01:02:57,183
Linda's diary.

1222
01:02:57,207 --> 01:02:59,152
She wrote about me in there?

1223
01:02:59,176 --> 01:03:02,054
Mr. White, now, how's
it gonna look to people

1224
01:03:02,078 --> 01:03:03,690
if they found out you
had an affair with her

1225
01:03:03,714 --> 01:03:04,924
and then she broke it off,

1226
01:03:04,948 --> 01:03:06,793
and then she tried to take
over your news program

1227
01:03:06,817 --> 01:03:08,128
and get you fired.

1228
01:03:08,152 --> 01:03:12,265
I mean, it looks like you
have a motive for murder.

1229
01:03:12,289 --> 01:03:14,000
Now, seriously,

1230
01:03:14,024 --> 01:03:16,458
wouldn't you really
rather talk to me, hm?

1231
01:03:19,696 --> 01:03:23,243
Look, it took me a
while to figure out

1232
01:03:23,267 --> 01:03:27,112
what a... user she was.

1233
01:03:27,136 --> 01:03:29,315
But she didn't break up with me.

1234
01:03:29,339 --> 01:03:30,616
I'm the one who called it off,

1235
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:33,441
when I found out
she was after my job.

1236
01:03:35,112 --> 01:03:36,155
Isn't that in there too?

1237
01:03:36,179 --> 01:03:37,524
No.

1238
01:03:37,548 --> 01:03:38,892
It's not?

1239
01:03:38,916 --> 01:03:40,347
No, it's not.

1240
01:03:41,685 --> 01:03:44,953
Well, thanks for your time.

1241
01:03:46,089 --> 01:03:47,322
Oh,

1242
01:03:49,459 --> 01:03:51,871
here's the subpoena,
just in case.

1243
01:03:55,765 --> 01:03:57,310
What did you find
when you arrived

1244
01:03:57,334 --> 01:03:58,611
at the decedent's apartment?

1245
01:03:58,635 --> 01:04:01,381
Miss Coolidge was lying
on the living room floor

1246
01:04:01,405 --> 01:04:03,082
bleeding from a chest wound.

1247
01:04:03,106 --> 01:04:05,151
Mm-hm. Did you
summon medical help?

1248
01:04:05,175 --> 01:04:06,485
The security guard

1249
01:04:06,509 --> 01:04:09,122
at the apartment complex
had already done that.

1250
01:04:09,146 --> 01:04:11,056
The paramedics
arrived shortly after I did.

1251
01:04:11,080 --> 01:04:12,725
They determined she was dead.

1252
01:04:12,749 --> 01:04:14,449
Mm-hm.

1253
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:18,253
I show you People's Exhibit 2...

1254
01:04:20,557 --> 01:04:22,335
and ask if you recognize it.

1255
01:04:22,359 --> 01:04:25,138
Yes, that's a .38
caliber revolver.

1256
01:04:25,162 --> 01:04:27,440
Was a ballistics test
performed on this revolver?

1257
01:04:27,464 --> 01:04:28,707
Yes, it was.

1258
01:04:28,731 --> 01:04:30,343
What was the
result of that test?

1259
01:04:30,367 --> 01:04:32,511
Ballistics tests
determined that the bullet

1260
01:04:32,535 --> 01:04:35,381
removed from Miss Coolidge's
chest was fired from that gun.

1261
01:04:35,405 --> 01:04:37,583
Where was this gun found?

1262
01:04:37,607 --> 01:04:39,318
On the floorboard
of a rented car

1263
01:04:39,342 --> 01:04:41,521
parked outside of the
apartment complex.

1264
01:04:41,545 --> 01:04:45,458
To whom was this
car rented at the time?

1265
01:04:45,482 --> 01:04:47,916
Mr. Steve Emerson.

1266
01:04:51,854 --> 01:04:53,134
Thank you.

1267
01:04:55,692 --> 01:04:57,057
No further questions.

1268
01:04:58,295 --> 01:04:59,739
Your witness.

1269
01:04:59,763 --> 01:05:02,029
No questions, Your Honor.

1270
01:05:09,172 --> 01:05:10,716
Mr. McCall.

1271
01:05:10,740 --> 01:05:12,084
Oh, hello. What is it?

1272
01:05:12,108 --> 01:05:13,820
You've been quite a
help to Steve Emerson.

1273
01:05:13,844 --> 01:05:15,087
We're all very grateful.

1274
01:05:15,111 --> 01:05:16,823
Oh, well, I'm sure he'd
do the same for me.

1275
01:05:16,847 --> 01:05:19,058
No, really. You've
gone out of your way.

1276
01:05:19,082 --> 01:05:21,594
Well, uh, no, it
was nothing, really.

1277
01:05:21,618 --> 01:05:22,929
Listen, would you excuse me?

1278
01:05:22,953 --> 01:05:25,364
'Cause, uh, I have some
people waiting for me.

1279
01:05:25,388 --> 01:05:27,066
But as helpful as
you've been to Steve,

1280
01:05:27,090 --> 01:05:29,501
I can never seem to
pinpoint you for an interview.

1281
01:05:29,525 --> 01:05:31,003
Well, that is
because, young lady,

1282
01:05:31,027 --> 01:05:33,172
I have nothing to add
that would be very useful,

1283
01:05:33,196 --> 01:05:34,373
I'm afraid.

1284
01:05:34,397 --> 01:05:37,143
Now, if you will excuse me,

1285
01:05:37,167 --> 01:05:38,544
I am running a bit late.

1286
01:05:38,568 --> 01:05:40,746
Gee, you could always
find time for Linda Coolidge

1287
01:05:40,770 --> 01:05:43,071
in the middle of the
afternoon, couldn't you.

1288
01:05:47,077 --> 01:05:49,488
Just what the hell is
that supposed to mean?

1289
01:05:49,512 --> 01:05:52,858
This makes for
very good reading.

1290
01:05:52,882 --> 01:05:53,882
Hm.

1291
01:05:55,118 --> 01:05:56,629
All right, why don't
you just tell me

1292
01:05:56,653 --> 01:05:58,665
what it is you want from me, hm?

1293
01:05:58,689 --> 01:05:59,832
I'm just curious.

1294
01:05:59,856 --> 01:06:01,500
When Linda Coolidge
broke off your affair,

1295
01:06:01,524 --> 01:06:03,369
were you so angry
that you murdered her?

1296
01:06:04,761 --> 01:06:05,960
She wasn't worth it.

1297
01:06:07,597 --> 01:06:09,241
Although I did, uh...

1298
01:06:09,265 --> 01:06:12,700
Yeah, I threw away a
15-year marriage for her.

1299
01:06:14,537 --> 01:06:17,783
And I suppose there
was a moment when I...

1300
01:06:17,807 --> 01:06:20,019
I would have loved
to have killed her.

1301
01:06:20,043 --> 01:06:22,355
But I, uh...

1302
01:06:22,379 --> 01:06:24,790
Well, I guess I
just wasn't up to it.

1303
01:06:26,816 --> 01:06:27,860
Satisfied?

1304
01:06:27,884 --> 01:06:29,562
Pretty much.

1305
01:06:29,586 --> 01:06:32,086
But here's a
subpoena, just in case.

1306
01:06:36,093 --> 01:06:38,404
Now, Mrs. Harris,

1307
01:06:38,428 --> 01:06:41,674
you testified that you saw
Steve Emerson, the defendant,

1308
01:06:41,698 --> 01:06:43,909
enter Linda Coolidge's apartment

1309
01:06:43,933 --> 01:06:46,078
at exactly 9:30
p.m., is that correct?

1310
01:06:46,102 --> 01:06:47,613
Yes, sir, it is.

1311
01:06:47,637 --> 01:06:50,917
How did you fix
on that exact time?

1312
01:06:50,941 --> 01:06:54,153
There's a clock on
top of my television set.

1313
01:06:54,177 --> 01:06:56,455
Oh, I see. I see.

1314
01:06:56,479 --> 01:06:58,091
You were looking at TV,

1315
01:06:58,115 --> 01:07:01,794
and when the program was
over you took your dog for a walk,

1316
01:07:01,818 --> 01:07:02,794
is that correct?

1317
01:07:02,818 --> 01:07:03,896
Yes, it is.

1318
01:07:03,920 --> 01:07:05,264
Well, that certainly explains

1319
01:07:05,288 --> 01:07:08,334
why you're so precise
as to the time. Hm.

1320
01:07:08,358 --> 01:07:10,937
Uh, now, Mrs.
Harris, you testified

1321
01:07:10,961 --> 01:07:14,774
that before the
gunshot, at 10:15,

1322
01:07:14,798 --> 01:07:19,045
you heard Steve Emerson
and Linda Coolidge arguing.

1323
01:07:19,069 --> 01:07:20,179
That's right.

1324
01:07:20,203 --> 01:07:22,815
Could you make out
what they were saying?

1325
01:07:22,839 --> 01:07:28,153
Well, I couldn't make it
out, but it sounded angry.

1326
01:07:28,177 --> 01:07:30,990
Well, how do you know it
was Steve Emerson's voice?

1327
01:07:31,014 --> 01:07:34,660
Well, I've been watching
him on television for years.

1328
01:07:34,684 --> 01:07:36,629
I recognized it.

1329
01:07:36,653 --> 01:07:40,432
Mrs. Harris, isn't it true

1330
01:07:40,456 --> 01:07:43,135
that you fixed the
time of the gunshot

1331
01:07:43,159 --> 01:07:45,237
because you were looking at TV

1332
01:07:45,261 --> 01:07:47,540
and you saw that clock
you were talking about?

1333
01:07:47,564 --> 01:07:49,475
Yes.

1334
01:07:49,499 --> 01:07:51,444
Mrs. Harris,

1335
01:07:51,468 --> 01:07:55,548
how can you be looking
at and listening to TV,

1336
01:07:55,572 --> 01:07:57,583
and identify Steve
Emerson's voice

1337
01:07:57,607 --> 01:07:59,685
through the apartment wall?

1338
01:07:59,709 --> 01:08:01,542
I heard him.

1339
01:08:05,849 --> 01:08:10,263
I suppose you can
assume it was his voice,

1340
01:08:10,287 --> 01:08:12,565
since you saw him
enter the apartment,

1341
01:08:12,589 --> 01:08:15,001
45 minutes earlier.

1342
01:08:15,025 --> 01:08:17,158
That's right.

1343
01:08:18,662 --> 01:08:20,194
Thank you, Mrs. Harris.

1344
01:08:21,798 --> 01:08:23,918
No further questions,
Your Honor.

1345
01:08:24,934 --> 01:08:27,113
You may be excused.

1346
01:08:29,739 --> 01:08:32,085
Do you wanna tell me
why you let her off so easy?

1347
01:08:32,109 --> 01:08:34,387
I made my point.

1348
01:08:34,411 --> 01:08:36,155
If I had kept after
her, she'd have dug in

1349
01:08:36,179 --> 01:08:38,191
and stuck to her story
come hell or high water.

1350
01:08:38,215 --> 01:08:41,015
Look like I was harassing
a nice, sweet lady.

1351
01:08:45,155 --> 01:08:47,621
Could you tell me if she
sublet her apartment to anyone?

1352
01:08:50,093 --> 01:08:51,870
No. No, I wouldn't
be interested.

1353
01:08:51,894 --> 01:08:53,194
Thank you.

1354
01:08:56,032 --> 01:08:57,075
Where have you been?

1355
01:08:57,099 --> 01:08:59,645
Oh, Corporations Commission.

1356
01:08:59,669 --> 01:09:00,779
How did it go today

1357
01:09:00,803 --> 01:09:02,548
with the flashing that
phony diary around?

1358
01:09:02,572 --> 01:09:03,882
Not great.

1359
01:09:03,906 --> 01:09:06,518
Both McCall and White
thought it was the real thing.

1360
01:09:06,542 --> 01:09:09,288
So I guess that eliminates them.

1361
01:09:09,312 --> 01:09:11,824
Maybe I should
try it on Lockwood.

1362
01:09:11,848 --> 01:09:13,893
The boyfriend? Why?

1363
01:09:13,917 --> 01:09:16,695
Well, if he and Linda were to be
married at the end of the month,

1364
01:09:16,719 --> 01:09:18,830
why would she make
plans to sublet her apartment

1365
01:09:18,854 --> 01:09:19,965
and then go to New York?

1366
01:09:19,989 --> 01:09:22,702
Maybe Mr. Lockwood
was gonna go with her.

1367
01:09:22,726 --> 01:09:24,270
And walk away from his business?

1368
01:09:24,294 --> 01:09:27,094
Maybe. And maybe not.

1369
01:09:28,698 --> 01:09:30,509
So where you going now?

1370
01:09:30,533 --> 01:09:32,711
I'm gonna go try
this on Lockwood.

1371
01:09:32,735 --> 01:09:34,346
Let me go with you.

1372
01:09:34,370 --> 01:09:35,781
No way, Tyler.

1373
01:09:35,805 --> 01:09:37,338
This one's on me.

1374
01:09:38,608 --> 01:09:40,274
Hm.

1375
01:09:45,682 --> 01:09:49,227
So at no time did you
ever see Mr. Emerson

1376
01:09:49,251 --> 01:09:50,696
leave the building?

1377
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:52,665
Uh, no, I did not.

1378
01:09:52,689 --> 01:09:56,302
And from the position
of your desk in the lobby,

1379
01:09:56,326 --> 01:09:58,537
he would have
had to pass by you.

1380
01:09:58,561 --> 01:10:00,072
That's right.

1381
01:10:00,096 --> 01:10:01,996
And you never left your desk.

1382
01:10:03,867 --> 01:10:07,112
Uh, not until I got the
call about the gunshot.

1383
01:10:07,136 --> 01:10:08,303
Right.

1384
01:10:09,472 --> 01:10:10,650
Thank you.

1385
01:10:10,674 --> 01:10:11,906
No further questions.

1386
01:10:12,975 --> 01:10:13,975
Your witness.

1387
01:10:16,479 --> 01:10:18,991
Mr. Banning,

1388
01:10:19,015 --> 01:10:21,894
how does a person gain
access to your building?

1389
01:10:21,918 --> 01:10:25,130
Uh, either through
the front entrance

1390
01:10:25,154 --> 01:10:27,666
or, if they have a key,
the garage elevator.

1391
01:10:27,690 --> 01:10:30,570
All right. Who has these keys?

1392
01:10:30,594 --> 01:10:31,594
The tenants.

1393
01:10:32,929 --> 01:10:35,541
Do you know how many keys
were issued to Linda Coolidge?

1394
01:10:35,565 --> 01:10:37,576
Two, I believe.

1395
01:10:37,600 --> 01:10:39,800
Heh. Thank you, Mr. Banning.

1396
01:10:40,637 --> 01:10:42,570
Oh, by the way,

1397
01:10:44,541 --> 01:10:47,787
are you familiar with
the<i> National Informer?</i>

1398
01:10:47,811 --> 01:10:49,243
Am I what?

1399
01:10:51,014 --> 01:10:53,280
Have you ever read
the<i> National Informer</i>?

1400
01:10:54,517 --> 01:10:56,517
Uh... Oh...

1401
01:10:58,989 --> 01:11:00,554
Well, ye... Yes.

1402
01:11:02,325 --> 01:11:05,571
Isn't it true that reporters
and photographers

1403
01:11:05,595 --> 01:11:07,840
were at the entrance
to your building

1404
01:11:07,864 --> 01:11:10,843
shortly after
Mr. Emerson arrived?

1405
01:11:10,867 --> 01:11:13,246
Uh, I believe so, yes.

1406
01:11:13,270 --> 01:11:16,148
Now, Mr. Banning,
it's my understanding

1407
01:11:16,172 --> 01:11:19,318
that, uh, publications,
ahem, like the<i> Informer,</i>

1408
01:11:19,342 --> 01:11:21,787
ones that deal in
gossip and such,

1409
01:11:21,811 --> 01:11:24,757
frequently pay
people to alert them

1410
01:11:24,781 --> 01:11:27,526
as to the comings and
goings of celebrities.

1411
01:11:27,550 --> 01:11:30,095
Now, that's always
seemed curious to me,

1412
01:11:30,119 --> 01:11:35,167
that they got there so soon
after Mr. Emerson arrived.

1413
01:11:35,191 --> 01:11:38,559
How do you suppose
they knew he was there?

1414
01:11:39,795 --> 01:11:42,141
I-I don't know.

1415
01:11:44,767 --> 01:11:46,645
I want you to
think very carefully

1416
01:11:46,669 --> 01:11:49,682
before you answer
this next question.

1417
01:11:49,706 --> 01:11:52,473
Did you call them the
night of the murder?

1418
01:11:57,013 --> 01:11:58,524
No.

1419
01:11:58,548 --> 01:12:02,583
Have you ever received money
from the<i> National Informer?</i>

1420
01:12:03,386 --> 01:12:04,386
No.

1421
01:12:07,023 --> 01:12:08,067
Sir, would you stand?

1422
01:12:09,425 --> 01:12:11,137
Do you recognize that gentleman

1423
01:12:11,161 --> 01:12:14,962
as Mr. J.L. Dupree of
the<i> National Informer?</i>

1424
01:12:18,435 --> 01:12:20,112
Uh, no.

1425
01:12:20,136 --> 01:12:24,016
Now, the<i> National Informer</i>
keeps very careful records

1426
01:12:24,040 --> 01:12:27,352
of all cash disbursements.

1427
01:12:27,376 --> 01:12:30,089
Before I call
Mr. Dupree to the stand,

1428
01:12:30,113 --> 01:12:32,724
I want to give you
the opportunity

1429
01:12:32,748 --> 01:12:36,328
to reconsider your testimony.

1430
01:12:36,352 --> 01:12:40,287
And remember, you're under oath.

1431
01:12:43,326 --> 01:12:45,960
Did you call them the
night of the murder?

1432
01:12:54,303 --> 01:12:55,803
Did you call 'em?

1433
01:12:57,106 --> 01:12:58,106
Well...

1434
01:13:00,443 --> 01:13:02,388
Yes. And when they arrived,

1435
01:13:02,412 --> 01:13:04,623
you met them at
the front entrance,

1436
01:13:04,647 --> 01:13:06,792
talked with them and
they gave you money.

1437
01:13:06,816 --> 01:13:08,494
Isn't that correct?

1438
01:13:08,518 --> 01:13:10,295
Yes. And while you were absent

1439
01:13:10,319 --> 01:13:12,398
from your desk,
Mr. Emerson could have

1440
01:13:12,422 --> 01:13:14,800
come down to the lobby,
seen them at the entrance,

1441
01:13:14,824 --> 01:13:17,736
gone out a side
door. Isn't that so?

1442
01:13:17,760 --> 01:13:20,105
I was only gone a moment.

1443
01:13:20,129 --> 01:13:22,329
No further questions,
Your Honor.

1444
01:13:23,299 --> 01:13:25,065
You can step down.

1445
01:13:26,936 --> 01:13:30,483
Court will recess until 9
a.m. tomorrow morning.

1446
01:13:34,343 --> 01:13:36,088
Thanks for stopping by, O.J.

1447
01:13:36,112 --> 01:13:37,155
This is Steve Emerson.

1448
01:13:37,179 --> 01:13:39,058
Oh, big fan of yours.
Hi, how are you?

1449
01:13:39,082 --> 01:13:40,693
Anyway, thanks for stopping by.

1450
01:13:40,717 --> 01:13:42,527
Go ahead and order
that field corn for me,

1451
01:13:42,551 --> 01:13:43,796
and I'll settle up next week.

1452
01:13:43,820 --> 01:13:45,319
Sure thing. Deal.

1453
01:13:46,989 --> 01:13:48,667
Field corn, huh?

1454
01:13:48,691 --> 01:13:50,903
I didn't say he was from
the<i> National Informer.</i>

1455
01:13:50,927 --> 01:13:52,805
I just asked him if
he recognized him

1456
01:13:52,829 --> 01:13:55,741
from the<i> National Informer.</i>

1457
01:13:55,765 --> 01:13:58,410
Congratulations, Matlock.

1458
01:13:58,434 --> 01:14:00,612
You made quite a run at
discrediting Mrs. Harris,

1459
01:14:00,636 --> 01:14:03,482
hearing Emerson, totally
impeached Banning.

1460
01:14:03,506 --> 01:14:05,183
Very slick stuff.

1461
01:14:05,207 --> 01:14:07,019
Coming from you that's
quite a compliment.

1462
01:14:07,043 --> 01:14:08,854
But I'll tell you something.
I really don't see

1463
01:14:08,878 --> 01:14:12,825
how you're going to get around
not having a convincing alibi.

1464
01:14:12,849 --> 01:14:14,993
And that gun in the car.

1465
01:14:17,854 --> 01:14:19,253
See you tomorrow.

1466
01:14:22,091 --> 01:14:24,611
What are we gonna do about that?

1467
01:14:25,562 --> 01:14:29,329
Oh, we might have a
few surprises left in us.

1468
01:14:30,867 --> 01:14:32,210
I hope so.

1469
01:14:41,577 --> 01:14:43,422
- Where's Charlene?
- I don't know. Why?

1470
01:14:43,446 --> 01:14:45,624
My unimpeachable sources

1471
01:14:45,648 --> 01:14:48,727
say the mob is funding a
big coastal resort project

1472
01:14:48,751 --> 01:14:51,297
currently under review by the
Land Development Commission.

1473
01:14:51,321 --> 01:14:53,232
Anybody on the
commission we know?

1474
01:14:53,256 --> 01:14:54,533
Ah, Mr. Lockwood.

1475
01:14:54,557 --> 01:14:56,869
Mr. Lockwood is a
dollar-a-year man for the state.

1476
01:14:56,893 --> 01:14:58,504
Head of the Land
Development Commission.

1477
01:14:58,528 --> 01:15:01,039
All right. Not so all right.

1478
01:15:01,063 --> 01:15:02,474
Last time I talked to Charlene,

1479
01:15:02,498 --> 01:15:05,244
she was on her way out there
to try that diary on Lockwood.

1480
01:15:23,152 --> 01:15:24,129
I don't know about you,

1481
01:15:24,153 --> 01:15:26,397
but I'm going home now.

1482
01:15:26,421 --> 01:15:28,781
He knows I'm still waiting.

1483
01:15:29,058 --> 01:15:30,335
He knows.

1484
01:15:30,359 --> 01:15:32,070
Well, thanks.

1485
01:15:32,094 --> 01:15:33,627
Bye.

1486
01:15:47,143 --> 01:15:49,788
Mr. Lockwood, I really
do have to talk to you.

1487
01:15:49,812 --> 01:15:51,090
What do you want?

1488
01:15:51,114 --> 01:15:53,459
Did you have a serious
falling out with Linda Coolidge?

1489
01:15:53,483 --> 01:15:56,828
I really don't know
what you're talking about.

1490
01:15:56,852 --> 01:15:59,665
She made an entry
in her diary about you

1491
01:15:59,689 --> 01:16:01,600
that I really don't understand.

1492
01:16:01,624 --> 01:16:03,068
Her what?

1493
01:16:03,092 --> 01:16:05,137
Her diary. This.

1494
01:16:05,161 --> 01:16:06,539
What is that?

1495
01:16:06,563 --> 01:16:07,843
You don't recognize her diary?

1496
01:16:11,801 --> 01:16:13,379
What kind of a game
are you playing?

1497
01:16:18,708 --> 01:16:21,028
We will see you in
court, Mr. Lockwood.

1498
01:17:14,029 --> 01:17:15,841
<i>Matlock and Matlock.</i>

1499
01:17:15,865 --> 01:17:17,075
<i>At the sound of the tone,</i>

1500
01:17:17,099 --> 01:17:18,844
<i>please leave your
name and number.</i>

1501
01:17:19,935 --> 01:17:21,980
Ben, hi. Uh, it... It's me.

1502
01:17:22,004 --> 01:17:24,650
It's about 8:15 tonight.

1503
01:17:24,674 --> 01:17:26,652
Well, Lockwood's our man.

1504
01:17:26,676 --> 01:17:30,255
He, um... He recognized that
the diary was a phony write-off.

1505
01:17:30,279 --> 01:17:31,857
Anyway, he must
have been the one

1506
01:17:31,881 --> 01:17:34,325
that took it from
Linda's apartment.

1507
01:17:34,349 --> 01:17:38,063
I'm gonna go check
out his office to s...

1508
01:19:38,908 --> 01:19:39,885
Are you all right?

1509
01:19:39,909 --> 01:19:41,674
He did it, Ben. He killed her.

1510
01:19:43,579 --> 01:19:46,680
What are you people
doing in my plant?

1511
01:19:50,719 --> 01:19:52,364
You sure you're all right? Yeah.

1512
01:19:52,388 --> 01:19:55,200
It would seem to me
you're trespassing.

1513
01:19:55,224 --> 01:19:57,223
I think you'd better leave.

1514
01:19:58,961 --> 01:20:00,081
Let's go.

1515
01:20:08,170 --> 01:20:10,090
I'll be with you in a minute.

1516
01:20:11,907 --> 01:20:13,051
You're all right?

1517
01:20:13,075 --> 01:20:14,140
Yeah.

1518
01:20:30,159 --> 01:20:33,338
Would you have risked your
neck like that for any other client?

1519
01:20:33,362 --> 01:20:37,464
Oh, Dad, don't start
on me. Not now.

1520
01:20:38,801 --> 01:20:40,946
I know it's none of my business,

1521
01:20:40,970 --> 01:20:42,814
and he's a nice
enough guy, I guess,

1522
01:20:42,838 --> 01:20:45,338
but he's here now
because he has to be.

1523
01:20:48,377 --> 01:20:52,558
If he acquitted, he's going
to go back to his own life.

1524
01:20:52,582 --> 01:20:56,194
I said my piece, and I
won't mention it again.

1525
01:20:56,218 --> 01:20:57,284
I promise.

1526
01:21:00,156 --> 01:21:02,055
I'm sure glad you're all right.

1527
01:21:04,793 --> 01:21:06,638
Okay.

1528
01:21:08,664 --> 01:21:11,332
Get some rest. We got a
lot of work to do tomorrow.

1529
01:21:35,257 --> 01:21:38,469
I wanna nail Lockwood to
the side of the barn so bad,

1530
01:21:38,493 --> 01:21:39,470
I can taste it.

1531
01:21:39,494 --> 01:21:41,173
But we don't have anything.

1532
01:21:41,197 --> 01:21:42,440
Nothing at all.

1533
01:21:42,464 --> 01:21:44,109
Well, Lockwood had
motive and access.

1534
01:21:44,133 --> 01:21:45,376
So did Steve.

1535
01:21:45,400 --> 01:21:47,880
Whose side are you on?
Right now I'm on the jury.

