And if we put
this solid citizen,

1537
01:21:50,239 --> 01:21:51,917
the grieved fiancé, on the stand

1538
01:21:51,941 --> 01:21:53,518
and grill him over the hot coals

1539
01:21:53,542 --> 01:21:55,387
without so much
as a workable theory

1540
01:21:55,411 --> 01:21:57,089
of how he might
have killed this woman,

1541
01:21:57,113 --> 01:22:01,359
then I'm gonna say let's convict
Steve Emerson and go home.

1542
01:22:01,383 --> 01:22:02,860
I wanna put Paul
Lockwood on the stand,

1543
01:22:02,884 --> 01:22:05,185
but we don't have a
dime's worth of anything.

1544
01:22:06,855 --> 01:22:08,166
Well, he was
supposed to have been

1545
01:22:08,190 --> 01:22:10,002
at this fundraiser at
the Mayfair all evening.

1546
01:22:10,026 --> 01:22:11,904
How do we get around
that? Tyler's down there now

1547
01:22:11,928 --> 01:22:15,773
trying to find anybody who
saw him leave before 10:15.

1548
01:22:15,797 --> 01:22:18,276
Charlene said there was
some TV news footage

1549
01:22:18,300 --> 01:22:20,412
taken outside the
apartment building that night.

1550
01:22:20,436 --> 01:22:22,113
It's at the station.

1551
01:22:22,137 --> 01:22:23,482
Can we look at it?

1552
01:22:23,506 --> 01:22:25,216
I'm sure McCall would cooperate.

1553
01:22:25,240 --> 01:22:27,741
Anything to avoid
his day in court.

1554
01:22:33,115 --> 01:22:35,961
Yo, folks, what do we
got on the tube, here?

1555
01:22:35,985 --> 01:22:38,797
Uh, rough news footage
from the night of the murder.

1556
01:22:38,821 --> 01:22:40,132
Fifteenth time.

1557
01:22:40,156 --> 01:22:41,899
What did you find
out at the hotel?

1558
01:22:41,923 --> 01:22:44,069
None of the staff saw him leave.

1559
01:22:44,093 --> 01:22:47,105
That means we have to go
through the entire guest list.

1560
01:22:47,129 --> 01:22:48,707
That could take weeks.

1561
01:22:48,731 --> 01:22:50,141
Let's see it again.

1562
01:22:50,165 --> 01:22:51,643
Ready?

1563
01:22:51,667 --> 01:22:52,787
Hold it right there.

1564
01:22:53,768 --> 01:22:55,147
Now, you see the exit sign

1565
01:22:55,171 --> 01:22:57,415
behind Lockwood, there?

1566
01:22:57,439 --> 01:22:58,550
Maybe some of the people there

1567
01:22:58,574 --> 01:23:00,218
saw him slip out
or come back in.

1568
01:23:00,242 --> 01:23:01,986
No, no, we don't know
who all those people are.

1569
01:23:02,010 --> 01:23:03,010
Yeah.

1570
01:23:04,513 --> 01:23:06,191
Let me see all
this just once more.

1571
01:23:06,215 --> 01:23:08,293
I got a feeling there's
something we're overlooking.

1572
01:23:08,317 --> 01:23:09,883
One more time, real quick.

1573
01:23:11,487 --> 01:23:12,564
All right, hold that one.

1574
01:23:15,724 --> 01:23:16,764
Now that one.

1575
01:23:19,261 --> 01:23:20,261
Now, here.

1576
01:23:39,715 --> 01:23:41,214
Of course.

1577
01:23:42,351 --> 01:23:44,017
It was there all the time.

1578
01:23:45,287 --> 01:23:47,565
All right.

1579
01:23:47,589 --> 01:23:50,469
Let's do put
Mr. Lockwood on the stand.

1580
01:23:50,493 --> 01:23:53,672
Mr. Lockwood, you are chairman

1581
01:23:53,696 --> 01:23:56,775
of the Land Development
Commission, is that correct?

1582
01:23:56,799 --> 01:23:59,010
Yes, it is.

1583
01:23:59,034 --> 01:24:01,713
Is there currently
under deliberation,

1584
01:24:01,737 --> 01:24:05,349
uh, a petition to grant
a zoning variance

1585
01:24:05,373 --> 01:24:10,121
to something called the Georgia
Coastal Development Company?

1586
01:24:10,145 --> 01:24:11,990
Yes, there is.

1587
01:24:12,014 --> 01:24:14,459
Why do they want the variance?

1588
01:24:14,483 --> 01:24:17,428
This group of developers
is hoping to build a resort

1589
01:24:17,452 --> 01:24:20,220
on what has been restricted
beachfront property.

1590
01:24:21,256 --> 01:24:22,634
Are you aware

1591
01:24:22,658 --> 01:24:26,304
that the Georgia Coastal
Development Company

1592
01:24:26,328 --> 01:24:31,876
is a subsidiary of American
Unified Finance Corporation?

1593
01:24:31,900 --> 01:24:34,012
I didn't bring documentation

1594
01:24:34,036 --> 01:24:35,613
regarding these
matters with me...

1595
01:24:35,637 --> 01:24:38,216
Your Honor, I object on
the grounds of relevancy.

1596
01:24:38,240 --> 01:24:41,018
Ahem, Your Honor, I
will prove the relevancy

1597
01:24:41,042 --> 01:24:43,154
with this line of questioning.

1598
01:24:43,178 --> 01:24:44,589
Overruled.

1599
01:24:44,613 --> 01:24:46,191
Thank you.

1600
01:24:46,215 --> 01:24:50,428
Now, I have here a list

1601
01:24:50,452 --> 01:24:52,097
of the board of directors

1602
01:24:52,121 --> 01:24:54,666
of American Unified.

1603
01:24:54,690 --> 01:24:58,236
Are you aware that at least
four of these board members

1604
01:24:58,260 --> 01:25:01,373
are currently under
federal indictment

1605
01:25:01,397 --> 01:25:02,841
for income tax evasion?

1606
01:25:02,865 --> 01:25:04,643
No, I am not.

1607
01:25:04,667 --> 01:25:08,880
And do you realize
that those same men

1608
01:25:08,904 --> 01:25:10,782
have long criminal records?

1609
01:25:10,806 --> 01:25:12,416
No.

1610
01:25:12,440 --> 01:25:14,519
Now, Mr. Lockwood,

1611
01:25:14,543 --> 01:25:18,656
you had a close,
personal relationship

1612
01:25:18,680 --> 01:25:22,394
with Linda Coolidge,
is that correct?

1613
01:25:22,418 --> 01:25:23,828
We were to be married.

1614
01:25:23,852 --> 01:25:25,752
Did you have a key
to her apartment?

1615
01:25:27,056 --> 01:25:28,288
Yes, I did.

1616
01:25:30,292 --> 01:25:34,839
Now, Mr. Lockwood,
the night of the murder

1617
01:25:34,863 --> 01:25:38,476
you were at a fundraising
dinner downtown.

1618
01:25:38,500 --> 01:25:39,811
Yes.

1619
01:25:39,835 --> 01:25:41,412
Were you there all evening?

1620
01:25:41,436 --> 01:25:44,615
I left when I received word
that Linda had been shot.

1621
01:25:44,639 --> 01:25:47,318
I was asked to
identify the body.

1622
01:25:47,342 --> 01:25:48,820
But you didn't
leave before that?

1623
01:25:48,844 --> 01:25:50,355
No.

1624
01:25:50,379 --> 01:25:52,079
Your Honor,

1625
01:25:53,515 --> 01:25:57,061
we have some
audio-visual material

1626
01:25:57,085 --> 01:25:59,397
that's pertinent
to this witness.

1627
01:25:59,421 --> 01:26:02,233
May we have permission
to bring it into the court?

1628
01:26:02,257 --> 01:26:04,569
Your Honor, this
entire line of questioning

1629
01:26:04,593 --> 01:26:05,837
is totally irrelevant.

1630
01:26:05,861 --> 01:26:10,742
I will demonstrate the
relevancy with the demonstration.

1631
01:26:10,766 --> 01:26:13,044
Overruled.

1632
01:26:13,068 --> 01:26:14,568
This'll just take a minute.

1633
01:26:19,909 --> 01:26:21,786
Now, on this first screen,

1634
01:26:21,810 --> 01:26:26,246
we're gonna see news footage
taken at the fundraising dinner.

1635
01:26:27,082 --> 01:26:28,122
Hold it right there.

1636
01:26:29,618 --> 01:26:31,829
And on the second screen,

1637
01:26:31,853 --> 01:26:33,665
we'll see more news footage

1638
01:26:33,689 --> 01:26:35,133
in front of the
decedent's apartment

1639
01:26:35,157 --> 01:26:37,124
the night of the murder.

1640
01:26:38,693 --> 01:26:42,140
Okay... hold it right there.

1641
01:26:42,164 --> 01:26:43,841
See? There he is.

1642
01:26:43,865 --> 01:26:46,844
Going in to identify the body.

1643
01:26:46,868 --> 01:26:48,546
On the third screen,

1644
01:26:48,570 --> 01:26:51,316
more news footage
of Mr. Lockwood

1645
01:26:51,340 --> 01:26:54,519
coming out later, after
identifying the body.

1646
01:26:54,543 --> 01:26:55,553
Freeze it, Tyler.

1647
01:26:55,577 --> 01:26:57,655
Your Honor, I-I still fail

1648
01:26:57,679 --> 01:26:59,690
to see the
relevance of all this.

1649
01:26:59,714 --> 01:27:00,825
Counsel for the defense

1650
01:27:00,849 --> 01:27:02,693
is indulging in his
well-known habit

1651
01:27:02,717 --> 01:27:05,496
of turning a courtroom
into a sideshow.

1652
01:27:05,520 --> 01:27:08,766
Your Honor, this is
crucial to our defense.

1653
01:27:08,790 --> 01:27:11,135
If you'll bear with me
a few more minutes.

1654
01:27:11,159 --> 01:27:13,438
Overruled.

1655
01:27:13,462 --> 01:27:15,807
Mr. Lockwood,

1656
01:27:15,831 --> 01:27:18,343
isn't it true that you slipped
out of that banquet unseen?

1657
01:27:18,367 --> 01:27:19,877
No.

1658
01:27:19,901 --> 01:27:22,047
And didn't you go to
Linda Coolidge's apartment,

1659
01:27:22,071 --> 01:27:25,416
where you argued with her
over exposing your connection

1660
01:27:25,440 --> 01:27:28,085
to organized crime through
a proposed news story

1661
01:27:28,109 --> 01:27:30,055
with Steve Emerson? No.

1662
01:27:30,079 --> 01:27:31,689
Didn't you struggle
with her and kill her?

1663
01:27:31,713 --> 01:27:32,957
Absolutely not.

1664
01:27:32,981 --> 01:27:34,280
But Mr. Lockwood,

1665
01:27:35,784 --> 01:27:38,362
you see, here at the banquet
you were wearing a name tag

1666
01:27:38,386 --> 01:27:40,598
like the other guests.

1667
01:27:40,622 --> 01:27:42,767
When you went to her
apartment to identify the body,

1668
01:27:42,791 --> 01:27:44,869
you were not wearing a name tag.

1669
01:27:44,893 --> 01:27:46,203
However, when
you came out again,

1670
01:27:46,227 --> 01:27:48,005
you were wearing
a name tag again.

1671
01:27:48,029 --> 01:27:50,908
You know what I think?

1672
01:27:50,932 --> 01:27:53,144
I think during the
struggle with her,

1673
01:27:53,168 --> 01:27:54,679
before you killed her,

1674
01:27:54,703 --> 01:27:57,348
that name tag
came off your suit.

1675
01:27:57,372 --> 01:27:59,350
And when you came
back, as you say,

1676
01:27:59,374 --> 01:28:01,086
to identify the body,

1677
01:28:01,110 --> 01:28:04,088
you found that name
tag and put it back,

1678
01:28:04,112 --> 01:28:08,026
which is why you are
wearing it right there.

1679
01:28:16,758 --> 01:28:18,536
I'm not on trial here.

1680
01:28:18,560 --> 01:28:20,093
You got that part right.

1681
01:28:21,530 --> 01:28:23,675
I don't have to prove
your guilt here and now.

1682
01:28:23,699 --> 01:28:26,745
I leave that in the skillful
hands of the prosecution.

1683
01:28:26,769 --> 01:28:29,714
They'll find somebody who
saw you leave that dinner.

1684
01:28:29,738 --> 01:28:33,318
They may even find somebody
who saw you near Emerson's car

1685
01:28:33,342 --> 01:28:35,241
when you put the gun there.

1686
01:28:36,978 --> 01:28:38,356
I just have to show this jury

1687
01:28:38,380 --> 01:28:40,325
that there's more than
a reasonable doubt

1688
01:28:40,349 --> 01:28:43,794
that Steve Emerson
committed this crime.

1689
01:28:43,818 --> 01:28:47,399
And I suppose we have
you to thank for that.

1690
01:28:51,159 --> 01:28:53,440
No further questions,
Your Honor.

1691
01:29:09,344 --> 01:29:12,156
We find the
defendant not guilty.

1692
01:29:15,951 --> 01:29:17,911
Congratulations, Mr. Emerson.

1693
01:29:18,520 --> 01:29:20,387
Mr. Matlock.

1694
01:29:24,526 --> 01:29:25,592
Excuse me.

1695
01:29:28,964 --> 01:29:31,108
Congratulations, Mr. Emerson.
Can we have a statement?

1696
01:29:31,132 --> 01:29:33,210
This is obviously
a great day for me

1697
01:29:33,234 --> 01:29:34,311
and for the press in general.

1698
01:29:34,335 --> 01:29:36,413
I mean, we were
right down to the wire,

1699
01:29:36,437 --> 01:29:37,615
but we pulled it out.

1700
01:29:37,639 --> 01:29:39,083
You...? You have any plans now?

1701
01:29:39,107 --> 01:29:41,720
All I wanna do right now is I
want to get back to New York,

1702
01:29:41,744 --> 01:29:43,455
and I wanna get back to work.

1703
01:29:43,479 --> 01:29:44,956
Excuse me, miss.

1704
01:29:44,980 --> 01:29:47,091
You don't think this
will have any effect

1705
01:29:47,115 --> 01:29:49,561
on your returning to your show?
- I hope not.

1706
01:29:49,585 --> 01:29:51,696
What about the case? Do you
think Matlock did a good job?

1707
01:29:51,720 --> 01:29:53,531
- Yes, I do.
- What about rumors

1708
01:29:53,555 --> 01:29:54,699
of you and Matlock's daughter?

1709
01:29:54,723 --> 01:29:56,389
No comment.

1710
01:30:00,695 --> 01:30:02,340
Tyler, you coming?

1711
01:30:02,364 --> 01:30:03,644
Yo.

1712
01:30:07,702 --> 01:30:10,181
Well, this probably
won't be on TV tomorrow,

1713
01:30:10,205 --> 01:30:13,317
but I know what a great
job the both of you did,

1714
01:30:13,341 --> 01:30:15,453
so I'm taking you to dinner.

1715
01:30:15,477 --> 01:30:17,355
All right. Where are we going?

1716
01:30:17,379 --> 01:30:19,424
Santino's. Santino's?

1717
01:30:19,448 --> 01:30:21,091
That's some kind of
pickup joint, ain't it?

1718
01:30:21,115 --> 01:30:23,127
No, it's where we
yuppies go to unwind.

1719
01:30:23,151 --> 01:30:25,095
Yeah, haven't you ever
seen a beer commercial?

